Re: I broke my wallet, sends never confirm now.

Bitcointalk

2010-10-06 16:54:23 UTC - [11]Original Post

   Thatʼs going to be more of a SelectCoins thing.
   SVN rev 161 has a refinement to recursively determine if your own
   unconfirmed transactions can be spent.  This is needed because you
   should be able to spend your own change right away.
   The new recursive determination is: 0/unconfirmed can be spent if itʼs
   yours and all its dependencies are either in a block or also yours.
   Hereʼs a Windows build:
   [12]http://www.bitcoin.org/download/bitcoin-0.3.13.2-win32-setup.exe
   This version is an improvement if you already had a 0/unconfirmed
   transaction and might have already spent it.  If you were the original
   creator of a 0/unconfirmed transaction, you still need theymosʼ patch
   instead.
